<br>
Despite the fact that i'm NG (high elf cleric), i feel that because of the BULLSHIT alignment system that is on this server, Good is a largely invalid choice. WHY is it that Evil races cannot pick neutral alignments while even the greatest of good races (high elves and erudin erudites) have neutral options?<br>
<br>
It seems to me (and I AM getting off on a rant) that VI has catered to the 'Spank the the Dark Elf Monkey' crowd... YET AGAIN... Neriak for 2/3 of the life of the game was the best trade skill city in the game, had the best choice of spells. The faction system for Evil races is a JOKE. If your dark elf cannot walk freely into MOST cities in the world by level 30-35, you are just slacking off.<br>
<br>
I have a friend on my old server with a 52nd level DE necro who is ALLY in Rivervale, Erudin, Freeport, Most of Qeynos (Except the EVIL guard faction), Kaladim (except for rogue faction) Ak'Anon and Kelethin.<br>
<br>
IMO, they either need to take away neutral from erudites and high elves or allow DEs and ogres to have more neutral choices (why can't a RZ Ogre warrior be ON, TN, or DN? it doesn't make sense...)<br>
<br>
It seems to me that the VI staff has once again latched on the the Vampire-esque appeal of Dark Elves without really thinking it through. If you're evil.. be EVIL and PENALIZE GOOD RACES FOR HELPING EVIL.<br>
<br>
On a similar note, why can't Erollisi Marr clerics heal ANYONE? another thing that makes NO sense... she's the goddess of Love and Tolerance... a priestess of E Marr would help anyone, regardless of religion.<br>
<br>
Also! Why can't MithMarr clerics and Cazic Clerics help each other? Mith Marr rules over TRUTH! What keeps people truthful? FEAR!<br>
<br>
